[{"id":"VR796117","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two parallel, horizontal wires a vertical distance 3 d apart. The top wire carries a current of 4 I to the right. The bottom wire carries a current of I to the left. Point A is located about one third of the way between the bottom and top wires, closer to the bottom wire.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR796117.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two long parallel wires, each in the plane of the page, are separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 d\"><math alttext=\"3 d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The top wire carries current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 I\"><math alttext=\"4 I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> directed to the right, and the bottom wire carries current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> directed to the left. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> is also in the plane of the page,  located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> above the bottom wire. Which of the following correctly represents the magnitude of the magnetic field due to the wires at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR796117_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"